kom?: 
kom: Build: docker build -t apt-cacher .
kom: Run: docker run -d -p 3142:3142 --name apt-cacher-run apt-cacher
kom?: 
kom: and then you can run containers with:
kom: docker run -t -i --rm -e http_proxy http://dockerhost:3142/ debian bash
kom?: 
kom: Here, `dockerhost` is the IP address or FQDN of a host running the Docker daemon
kom: which acts as an APT proxy server.
FROM: ubuntu
VOLUME: /var/cache/apt-cacher-ng
RUN: apt-get update && apt-get install -y apt-cacher-ng
EXPOSE: 3142
CMD: chmod 777 /var/cache/apt-cacher-ng && /etc/init.d/apt-cacher-ng start && tail -f /var/log/apt-cacher-ng/*a